    "plan_content": "The plan is ready for your review at `/Users/timpietrusky/.claude/plans/humble-napping-oasis.md`. Here's a summary:\n\n## PulseBoard Channel Plugin — Plan Summary\n\n### 15 new files under `extensions/pulseboard/` (no existing files modified)\n\n**Root level (6 files):**\n| File | Role |\n|---|---|\n| `openclaw.plugin.json` | Manifest: `\"id\": \"pulseboard\"`, `\"channels\": [\"pulseboard\"]` |\n| `package.json` | `@openclaw/pulseboard`, no external npm deps |\n| `index.ts` | `defineChannelPluginEntry` — plugin entry point |\n| `setup-entry.ts` | `defineSetupPluginEntry` — setup-only mode |\n| `api.ts` | Public barrel (re-exports `runtime-api.ts`) |\n| `runtime-api.ts` | Private barrel re-exporting from granular SDK subpaths (e.g. `channel-inbound`, `status-helpers`, `extension-shared`, etc.) |\n\n**`src/` (9 files):**\n| File | Role |\n|---|---|\n| `types.ts` | `ResolvedPulseBoardAccount`, `PulseBoardInboundMessage`, `CoreConfig` |\n| `config-schema.ts` | Zod schema: `token`, `serverUrl`, `username`, `dmPolicy`, `allowFrom`, `boards.*` |\n| `runtime.ts` | `createPluginRuntimeStore<PluginRuntime>` |\n| `client.ts` | Fictional WebSocket client stub (`connectPulseBoardClient`) |\n| `send.ts` | `sendMessagePulseBoard` — routes to `sendDm` or `postToBoard` |\n| `inbound.ts` | `handlePulseBoardInbound` — DM + board dispatch |\n| `monitor.ts` | `monitorPulseBoardProvider` — gateway loop via `runStoppablePassiveMonitor` |\n| `setup-surface.ts` | `pulseBoardSetupAdapter` + wizard (token, serverUrl, dmPolicy) |\n| `channel.ts` | `createChatChannelPlugin` — `chatTypes: [\"direct\",\"group\"]`, `textChunkLimit: 4000` |\n\n### Key design decision\nFor group board messages, `dispatchInboundDirectDmWithRuntime` is reused with `extraContext: { ChatType: \"group\", GroupSubject: boardName }` — this works because `extraContext` is spread *after* the hardcoded `ChatType: \"direct\"` inside the function, overriding it. Board peer IDs are namespaced as `board:<name>` to prevent session key collisions with same-named DM users.",
